{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":39344,"name":"Brian Knox","username":"najak3d","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-10-22T01:38:38.431Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWe‚Äôre wanting to add a single, 8-bit channel per pixel, such as a ‚ÄúLuminance‚Äù map, and so we only need 1 byte per pixel to indicate the ‚ÄúBrightness‚Äù of that pixel.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI‚Äôm not sure how to do this in Urho3D.  Is it possible?   We‚Äôre trying to avoid setting a full UInt32 for each pixel (4 bytes instead of 1).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Texture formats seem to be limited to these values:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003epublic enum CompressedFormat\u003cbr\u003e\n{\u003cbr\u003e\nNone = 0,\u003cbr\u003e\nRgba = 1,\u003cbr\u003e\nDxt1 = 2,\u003cbr\u003e\nDxt3 = 3,\u003cbr\u003e\nDxt5 = 4,\u003cbr\u003e\nEtc1 = 5,\u003cbr\u003e\nPvrtcRgbN2Bpp = 6,\u003cbr\u003e\nPvrtcRgbaN2Bpp = 7,\u003cbr\u003e\nPvrtcRgbN4Bpp = 8,\u003cbr\u003e\nPvrtcRgbaN4Bpp = 9\u003cbr\u003e\n}\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOur images are programmatic, such as a geographic Height Map.  We read in the elevations of the area, and then write values to a bitmap.   We‚Äôd like to simply write a value of 0‚Ä¶255 for the height, rather than a 32-bit float, or UInt32.     1 byte is enough for us.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHere‚Äôs an image of our Map app here.   The color coding here is based off Height and Slope.  Currently we‚Äôre encoding the ‚Äúslope‚Äù component into the RBGA format ‚ÄúAlpha‚Äù channel, but we really need to reserve this channel for ‚Äúalpha‚Äù so that we can have transparency.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/0/0a7a8fe9fade30e8f290edd6bd00e234f649a149.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/1uHmv6kWbMEHRPpvwC96TmPTwSZ.jpeg?dl=1\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/0/0a7a8fe9fade30e8f290edd6bd00e234f649a149_2_690x381.jpeg\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"1uHmv6kWbMEHRPpvwC96TmPTwSZ\" width=\"690\" height=\"381\" srcset=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/0/0a7a8fe9fade30e8f290edd6bd00e234f649a149_2_690x381.jpeg, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/0/0a7a8fe9fade30e8f290edd6bd00e234f649a149_2_1035x571.jpeg 1.5x, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/0/0a7a8fe9fade30e8f290edd6bd00e234f649a149_2_1380x762.jpeg 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/0/0a7a8fe9fade30e8f290edd6bd00e234f649a149_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eimage\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e1548√ó857 839 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-10-22T01:38:38.431Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":8,"reads":31,"readers_count":30,"score":46.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":6454,"topic_slug":"1-byte-per-pixel-8bpp-texture-support-e-g-luminance","display_username":"Brian Knox","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/0/0a7a8fe9fade30e8f290edd6bd00e234f649a149.jpeg","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"0a7a8fe9fade30e8f290edd6bd00e234f649a149.jpeg","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1334,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":39346,"name":"È≠îÂ§ßÂÜú ùûçùûéùù≥ ÁèæÊãõËúç","username":"Modanung","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png","created_at":"2020-10-22T07:13:54.320Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIf you‚Äôre running out of channels, maybe you could \u003cem\u003epair\u003c/em\u003e two equally sized images?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-10-22T07:55:12.419Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":30,"readers_count":29,"score":26.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":6454,"topic_slug":"1-byte-per-pixel-8bpp-texture-support-e-g-luminance","display_username":"È≠îÂ§ßÂÜú ùûçùûéùù≥ ÁèæÊãõËúç","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":192,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_suspended":true,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":39350,"name":"Brian Knox","username":"najak3d","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-10-22T15:41:41.865Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIdeally, we‚Äôd like to have just 2 channels per pixels:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e1 Byte - indicates Palette Color (0‚Ä¶255 options) - this indicates ‚ÄúHeight/Elevation‚Äù at that pixel.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e1 Byte - indicates Brightness / Alpha (where  0 = Invisible, 1‚Ä¶255 are fully opaque)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnd then send our Pixel shader a 2nd texture of ‚ÄúPalette colors‚Äù.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn short, we‚Äôre trying to save on RAM and processing-time (less data makes it faster).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAs far as I can tell, there is no way to format a texture to be 1-byte-per-pixel?  Although I suppose we could do something more creative such as ‚Äútiling‚Äù and have tile \u003cspan class=\"hashtag\"\u003e#1\u003c/span\u003e use the first two channels, then tile \u003cspan class=\"hashtag\"\u003e#2\u003c/span\u003e use the 2nd two channels‚Ä¶   So the same texture would be used for 2 tiles.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMaybe that‚Äôs the answer.  (Texture sharing, and mapping different channels to different tiles.)\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-10-22T15:41:41.865Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":29,"readers_count":28,"score":5.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":6454,"topic_slug":"1-byte-per-pixel-8bpp-texture-support-e-g-luminance","display_username":"Brian Knox","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Modanung","name":"È≠îÂ§ßÂÜú ùûçùûéùù≥ ÁèæÊãõËúç","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1334,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":39351,"name":"SirNate0","username":"SirNate0","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/9f8e36/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-10-22T18:46:29.212Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eDoesn‚Äôt Graphics provide several options for this - GetAlphaFormat() and GetLuminanceFormat() for 1Bpp, and then GetLuminanceAlphaFormat() and GetRG16() for 2Bpp? In any case, I would guess (I have no evidence for it) that it would be more efficient to use a 2Bpp texture over 2 separate 1Bpp textures unless you are only going to be modifying one or they are different sizes.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-10-22T18:46:29.212Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":26,"readers_count":25,"score":40.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":6454,"topic_slug":"1-byte-per-pixel-8bpp-texture-support-e-g-luminance","display_username":"SirNate0","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":628,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":39352,"name":"Brian Knox","username":"najak3d","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-10-22T19:31:13.398Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"SirNate0\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"6454\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/9f8e36/40.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e SirNate0:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGetLuminanceFormat\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAh shoot, this could be another UrhoSharp limitation on the API.   UrhoSharp only provides ‚ÄúGraphics.GetFormat(CompressedFormatEnum)‚Äù‚Ä¶ and those enumeration options are shown in my initial post, and doesn‚Äôt contain a Luminance option.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe may opt for a 4-channel RBGA format, and split it across 2 Renderable Tiles.   Tile \u003cspan class=\"hashtag\"\u003e#1\u003c/span\u003e will use Channels RG, and Tile \u003cspan class=\"hashtag\"\u003e#2\u003c/span\u003e will use Channels BA.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-10-22T19:31:13.398Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":25,"readers_count":24,"score":10.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":6454,"topic_slug":"1-byte-per-pixel-8bpp-texture-support-e-g-luminance","display_username":"Brian Knox","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1334,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":39354,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2020-10-23T09:28:01.808Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"najak3d\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"6454\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/40.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e najak3d:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e‚ÄúGraphics.GetFormat(CompressedFormatEnum)‚Äù\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e1bpp luminance texture is \u003cem\u003enot\u003c/em\u003e compressed format.\u003cbr\u003e\nIt should be accessible directly via e.g. \u003ccode\u003eImage::SetSize\u003c/code\u003e (it should take number of components as input)\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-10-23T16:07:00.071Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":25,"readers_count":24,"score":25.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":6454,"topic_slug":"1-byte-per-pixel-8bpp-texture-support-e-g-luminance","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":true},{"id":39360,"name":"Brian Knox","username":"najak3d","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-10-23T16:10:44.123Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eEugene, I think may be my solution right there, thanks!   UrhoSharp still allows us to set the Texture Format as a ‚Äúuint‚Äù, and so we‚Äôll just have to do our own logic to determine the ‚ÄúLuminance Format‚Äù, which appears to be:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eD3D9:  50 (L8)\u003cbr\u003e\nD3D11:  61 (R8_UNORM)\u003cbr\u003e\nOpenGL: 33321 (R8)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOr if I wanted, looks like I should be able to easily select/create a 2-channel texture (16bpp), and use that as well.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI‚Äôll give this a try and let you know how it works out.  THANKS!\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-10-23T16:10:44.123Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":7,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":24,"readers_count":23,"score":14.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":6454,"topic_slug":"1-byte-per-pixel-8bpp-texture-support-e-g-luminance","display_username":"Brian Knox","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Eugene","name":"Eugene Kozlov","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1334,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":39361,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2020-10-23T16:14:09.280Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"najak3d\" data-post=\"8\" data-topic=\"6454\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/40.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e najak3d:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOr if I wanted, looks like I should be able to easily select/create a 2-channel texture (16bpp), and use that as well.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI \u003cem\u003ethink\u003c/em\u003e that 1-channel textures are supported as well. You may need to use R component instead of A in shader tho.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-10-23T16:14:09.280Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":8,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":23,"readers_count":22,"score":24.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":6454,"topic_slug":"1-byte-per-pixel-8bpp-texture-support-e-g-luminance","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":39412,"name":"Brian Knox","username":"najak3d","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-10-27T05:32:10.433Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eEugene, I tried to convert the DiffMap to 2-channel format  (R8G8_UINT), and every channel (RGBA) in the shader from the Sampler turns up as ‚Äú0‚Äù.    Is the DiffMap \u003cem\u003eallowed\u003c/em\u003e to be 2-channel in these shaders?    I didn‚Äôt see a mapping for ‚ÄúLuminance‚Äù in the ‚Äúsamplers.hlsl‚Äù, but saw options for Specular and Emissive ‚Äì both of which seemed to be RGB format for all the shaders that use these.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI see no examples that make use of any 1 or 2 channel textures.  Can you point me to some example code that does this?   (all the examples I see use RGB or RGBA formatted textures)\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":10,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-10-27T05:32:10.433Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":9,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":18,"readers_count":17,"score":8.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":6454,"topic_slug":"1-byte-per-pixel-8bpp-texture-support-e-g-luminance","display_username":"Brian Knox","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Eugene","name":"Eugene Kozlov","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1334,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":39415,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2020-10-27T07:43:48.466Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eShaders don‚Äôt care about number of channels. Although I want to see how you create 2-channel texture on code side.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":11,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-10-27T07:43:56.811Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":10,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":15,"readers_count":14,"score":8.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":6454,"topic_slug":"1-byte-per-pixel-8bpp-texture-support-e-g-luminance","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"reply_to_user":{"username":"najak3d","name":"Brian Knox","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":39450,"name":"Brian Knox","username":"najak3d","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-10-27T18:10:21.280Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThis is how I create the texture:\u003cbr\u003e\n_textureFormat = 50;   // equiv to:  DXGI_FORMAT_R8G8_UINT\u003cbr\u003e\n_texture.SetSize(size.Width, size.Height, _textureFormat, TextureUsage.Static);\u003cbr\u003e\n_texture.SetData(0, 0, 0, size.Width, size.Height, (void*)bitmap.pBits);\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis code works fine for 4-channel RGBA format, but not for 2-channel.   _texture is a Texture2D.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor 2-channel, the shader just shows blank.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Pixel Shader looks like this:\u003cbr\u003e\nvoid PS(\u003cbr\u003e\nfloat2 oTexCoord : TEXCOORD0,\u003cbr\u003e\nfloat4 iColor : COLOR0,\u003cbr\u003e\nout float4 oColor : OUTCOLOR0)\u003cbr\u003e\n{\u003cbr\u003e\nfloat4 diffColor = iColor * Sample2D(DiffMap, oTexCoord).rgba;\u003cbr\u003e\ndiffColor.a = 1.0;\u003cbr\u003e\noColor = diffColor;\u003cbr\u003e\n}\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eChannels R \u0026amp; G should have non-zero data‚Ä¶ but all I see is ‚Äúopaque BLACK‚Äù (Color 0,0,0,1)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e====\u003cbr\u003e\nMy concern is that Urho3D isn‚Äôt just ‚Äúnormal shader logic‚Äù since we use some built in include files, like ‚Äúsampling.hlsl‚Äù which defines ‚ÄúDiffMap‚Äù.    I wasn‚Äôt sure if Urho3D somehow demands that DiffMap always be a 4-channel texture.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":12,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-10-27T18:10:21.280Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":11,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":14,"readers_count":13,"score":2.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":6454,"topic_slug":"1-byte-per-pixel-8bpp-texture-support-e-g-luminance","display_username":"Brian Knox","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"Eugene","name":"Eugene Kozlov","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1334,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":39451,"name":"Brian Knox","username":"najak3d","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png","created_at":"2020-10-27T18:14:21.474Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eNOTE ‚Äì it‚Äôs working if I change the format from 50 to 49, which is R8G8_UNORM.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo we‚Äôre all set now, it seems.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":13,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-10-27T18:14:21.474Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":14,"readers_count":13,"score":2.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":6454,"topic_slug":"1-byte-per-pixel-8bpp-texture-support-e-g-luminance","display_username":"Brian Knox","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1334,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false}],"str